The main constituent of CP, i.e., BaCuSi2O6 (colinowensite) also crystallizes in the tetragonal system but unlike the other 2D alkaline-earth copper silicate described so far, is not a member of the gillespite-group and is not a phyllosilicate. Indeed, it is a cyclosilicate (Rieck et al. 2015). Its crystal structure has been at first assigned to space group I4¯4¯\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
